Package sample

Class Tile

  • java.lang.Object
    • sample.Tile
  • public class Tile
extends java.lang.Object

    This class is about creating a tile with XY values
    Besides that, this is where it converts the grid XY values to scene (UI) grid XY. So when i want a tile at 0,0, it will place the tile correctly at the right ui coordinates.

    Author:
    Lucas Kugelberg (Github: github.com/KugelbergDK)

      • getUICoordinates

        public int[] getUICoordinates()
        This method converts the Tile's XY values to the User Interface XY. Lets say we want to spawn a tile at 0,0 (On the game board). Without this method, it will be spawned at the top corner, that not what we want. When i designed the prototype in AdobeXD, I took the UI coordinates from there and inserted to the belonged tiles.
        Returns:
        XY coordinates to this tile. Index 0 is X-value, Index 1 is Y-value.
